---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const canonical = 'https://onlinephotocollage.com/about-us/';
---

<Layout
	title="About Us | Photo Collage Maker"
	description="Learn about Photo Collage Maker, a free online collage editor for creating Instagram collage stories, posts, and photo collage designs."
	canonical={canonical}
>
	<header class="pc-site-header">
		<a href="/" class="pc-site-header-brand" aria-label="Photo Collage home">
			<img src="/Icons/favicon.svg" alt="" width="30" height="30" loading="eager" decoding="async" />
			<span>Photo Collage</span>
		</a>
		<nav class="pc-site-header-links" aria-label="Website">
			<a href="/">Editor</a>
			<a href="/contact-us/">Contact</a>
			<a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy</a>
			<a href="/terms-and-conditions/">Terms</a>
		</nav>
	</header>

	<main class="pc-doc-page">
		<section class="pc-doc-container pc-doc-hero" aria-labelledby="about-title">
			<p class="pc-label">About us</p>
			<h1 id="about-title">A focused online photo collage maker</h1>
			<p>
				Photo Collage Maker helps people create clean collage designs directly in the browser, from Instagram collage stories and posts to simple memory pages, mood boards, and printable image layouts.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="pc-doc-container pc-doc-grid" aria-label="About Photo Collage Maker">
			<div class="pc-doc-body">
				<h2>Why we built it</h2>
				<p>
					Collage tools are often buried inside large design suites. We wanted a faster path: open the editor, choose a template, upload photos, adjust the layout, and download a finished image. The product is intentionally focused on collage creation so the workflow stays light and easy to understand.
				</p>
				<h2>What you can create</h2>
				<p>
					The editor supports Instagram collage story designs, Instagram collage post layouts, family collages, birthday recaps, travel boards, product highlights, and other photo-first visuals. You can use frames, text, stickers, backgrounds, and export options to make a collage that fits your use case.
				</p>
				<h2>Our approach</h2>
				<p>
					We keep the interface practical: templates on one side, the editable canvas in the center, and object controls nearby. The goal is to make collage editing feel approachable on desktop and mobile without unnecessary steps.
				</p>
			</div>

			<aside class="pc-doc-panel">
				<h2>Quick facts</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Browser-based photo collage editor.</li>
					<li>Templates for Instagram, social posts, and personal designs.</li>
					<li>No account required to start editing.</li>
					<li>PNG and JPG export support.</li>
				</ul>
			</aside>
		</section>
	</main>

	<footer class="pc-site-footer" aria-label="Website links">
		<div class="pc-site-footer-inner">
			<a href="/" class="pc-site-footer-brand" aria-label="Photo Collage home">
				<img src="/Icons/favicon.svg" alt="" width="28" height="28" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
				<span>Photo Collage</span>
			</a>
			<nav class="pc-site-footer-links" aria-label="Footer">
				<a href="/contact-us/">Contact us</a>
				<a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy policy</a>
				<a href="/terms-and-conditions/">Terms & conditions</a>
			</nav>
		</div>
	</footer>
</Layout>
